From 16fd5af763a26417e8d9e76531ff69d38df59c11 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <claude@tsm-consultz.local>
Date: Wed, 1 Jul 2026 21:54:35 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Disable auto-obfuscation workflow -- produces invalid JS

Confirmed via node --check: the obfuscator config (selfDefending +
controlFlowFlattening + stringArrayEncoding) generates syntactically
broken JavaScript -- an unescaped literal newline inside a single-quoted
string literal, which is illegal JS regardless of how a browser parses
it. Every inline <script> block in a touched file would throw and fail
to execute entirely.

This was about to auto-commit across 596 files (+2783/-85574) the
moment the github-actions[bot] permission issue got fixed. Caught it
first by extracting the obfuscated output from a real war room file
and syntax-checking it directly, rather than trusting the diff stats.

Not needed right now anyway -- everything is in-house, no external
distribution, so there's no IP-protection case for obfuscating at all
at this stage. Removed the push trigger, left workflow_dispatch so it
can be re-enabled manually if the config gets fixed and re-validated
later. build.js's path fix (HTML_DIR) stays -- harmless and correct
regardless of whether this workflow ever runs again.
---
 .github/workflows/obfuscate.yml | 19 ++++++++++---------
 1 file changed, 10 insertions(+), 9 deletions(-)

diff --git a/.github/workflows/obfuscate.yml b/.github/workflows/obfuscate.yml
index c7f0cab..3e0e03f 100644
--- a/.github/workflows/obfuscate.yml
+++ b/.github/workflows/obfuscate.yml
@@ -1,17 +1,18 @@
 # TSM Shell — Auto JS Obfuscation Pipeline
-# Runs on every push to main, obfuscates all inline <script> blocks
-# across /html, then commits the result back to the repo.
+# DISABLED 2026-07-01: the obfuscation config (selfDefending + controlFlowFlattening +
+# stringArrayEncoding) produces syntactically invalid JS -- confirmed via node --check
+# failing on the output. Auto-committing this to main would have broken every inline
+# <script> block across the app. Not needed right now anyway (in-house only, no IP
+# exposure). Left as workflow_dispatch-only so it can be re-enabled manually once the
+# obfuscator config is fixed and validated.
+#
+# Originally: ran on every push to main, obfuscated all inline <script> blocks
+# across /html, then committed the result back to the repo.
 
 name: Obfuscate JS
 
 on:
-  push:
-    branches: [main]
-    paths:
-      - 'html/**'          # only trigger when HTML files change
-      - 'build.js'         # or when the build script itself changes
-
-  workflow_dispatch:       # allow manual trigger from GitHub Actions tab
+  workflow_dispatch:       # manual trigger only -- push auto-trigger removed
 
 jobs:
   obfuscate:
-- 
